                <h3>I am the only one one the morgage but split it 50/50 with a roommate. Can I claim 100% of the morgage intrest? My roommate did not claim any on the morgage intrest, she did not think to because her name is not on the 1098. Can my roommate claim 50%?</h3>
                <hr align="left" style="border-color: black; width: 70%" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-1">
                <p>
                    The mortgage is in your name and the 1098 is in your name..ou are the one who has to claim it on your taxes.and it sounds is if your room mate may have already completed her taxes?
                    Anyway Mr. IRS,uncle Sam, knows one thing, which is your name when it pertains to the mortgage and the credit for the interest paid. it's up to you if you want to compensate the room mate some how:)
                </p>
